MongoDB Kubernetes Operator Setup

link : - https://github.com/mongodb/mongodb-kubernetes-operator/blob/master/docs/install-upgrade.md

Step 1 : git clone https://github.com/mongodb/mongodb-kubernetes-operator.git

Step 2 : cd mongodb-kubernetes-operator

Step 3 : kubectl apply -f config/crd/bases/mongodbcommunity.mongodb.com_mongodbcommunity.yaml

    kubectl get crd/mongodbcommunity.mongodbcommunity.mongodb.com

Step 4 : kubectl apply -k config/rbac/ 

    kubectl get role mongodb-kubernetes-operator
    kubectl get rolebinding mongodb-kubernetes-operator 
    kubectl get serviceaccount mongodb-kubernetes-operator 

Step 5 : kubectl create -f config/manager/manager.yaml

Step 6 : Configure edit pv.yaml and mongodb.com_v1_hostpath.yaml  // username ,passwords, pvc , resources,etc

Step 7 : kubectl apply -f /config/samples/arbitrary_statefulset_configuration/pv.yaml

Step 8 : kubectl apply -f /config/samples/arbitrary_statefulset_configuration/mongodb.com_v1_hostpath.yaml

Step 9 : wait for all pods to running

Step 10: kubectl edit svc mongo-svc 
   
   change name of svc from mongo-svc to mongo
